title: Spain believed to have hit hottest April day ever
description: Spain is believed to have recorded its hottest ever April day.

title: Pentagon leaks suspect 'discussed murder and assassination van'
description: A man accused of leaking US military documents had "troubling discussions" about violence and murder and said he was tempted to make an "assassination van", prosecutors say.

title: East Africa drought would not have happened without humans, new science says
description: The severe drought devastating the Horn of Africa by killing animals and crops and leaving millions without enough food would not have happened if humans had not heated the planet, scientists have concluded.

title: Man on luxury cruise ship goes overboard
description: A man has gone overboard on a luxury cruise ship passing through waters south of Hawaii.

title: 'Donald Trump raped me,' accuser tells court
description: A writer who claims Donald Trump raped her nearly three decades ago in a department store changing room has told a court: "I'm here to try and get my life back."

title: Pope Francis gives women vote in upcoming influential bishops' meeting
description: Pope Francis has approved changes that will allow women to vote at a global meeting of bishops for the first time.

title: Rival factions agree to ceasefire extension in Sudan - as UK evacuates almost 900
description: Sudan's rival factions have agreed to extend a 72-hour ceasefire - just hours before the original truce was due to end.

title: UK 'cannot guarantee' number of Sudan evacuation flights after ceasefire ends
description: British nationals in Sudan have been warned the UK "cannot guarantee" how many more evacuation flights will leave Khartoum after the 72-hour ceasefire expires.
